In [[medicine]], '''Goodell sign''' is an indication of [[pregnancy]]. It is a significant softening of the [[vagina]]l portion of the [[cervix]] from increased vascularization. This vascularization is a result of hypertrophy and engorgement of the vessels below the growing uterus. This sign occurs at approximately four weeks' gestation.
The sign is named after [[William Goodell (gynecologist)|William Goodell]].
==See also== * [[Chadwick's sign]] * [[Hegar's sign]] * [[Ladin's sign]]
