{{about|the remote collection of scientific data|the process of depositing a cheque to a bank by use of an image|Remote deposit}}

'''Remote data capture''' is the process of automatic collection of scientific data. It is widely used in clinic trials,<ref>''Welcome to the CTSU Remote Data Capture Project '' [http://www.ctsu.org/RDC_project_page.asp Cancer Trials Support Unit]</ref> where it is referred to as [[electronic data capture]]. In physical sciences, automatic observation hardware in the field can be linked to an observer in a laboratory through a [[cellphone]] or other communication link,<ref>''Water and global change'' [http://portal.unesco.org/science/es/ev.php-URL_ID=1322&URL_DO=DO_TOPIC&URL_SECTION=201.html Hydrology for Environment, Life and Policy]</ref> for example in [[hydrology]]. RDC systems influenced the design of later [[electronic data capture]] (EDC) systems.<ref>Aitkendhead, M.J. and Cooper, R.J. 2007. Neural network time series prediction of environmental variables in a small upland headwater in NE Scotland. ''Hydrological Processes'', '''22''', 3091-3101 [https://dx.doi.org/10.1002/hyp.6895] 
</ref>

